00:23:38,300 --> 00:23:41,000
bleed themselves dry,
And i can't have that, ok?

81
00:23:41,900 --> 00:23:43,500
It's not worth it.

82
00:23:44,600 --> 00:23:46,100
I'm not worth it.

83
00:23:46,300 --> 00:23:49,200
- What do you mean?
- It's too late, ok?

84
00:23:50,000 --> 00:23:51,900
Can you just tell him that?

85
00:23:52,000 --> 00:23:55,200
It's hard,
and it hurts too much.

86
00:23:55,700 --> 00:23:57,400
The best thing
that rick can do for me

87
00:23:57,400 --> 00:23:59,600
Is to find some peace for himself.

88
00:24:06,100 --> 00:24:08,100
I told him,
call a plumber,

89
00:24:08,100 --> 00:24:10,600
But no, he had to
fix the pipe by himself.

90
00:24:10,700 --> 00:24:12,700
Goes and falls
off a ladder.

91
00:24:16,100 --> 00:24:17,500
Hey, uh, buddy--
Wait.

92
00:24:17,600 --> 00:24:19,200
Look, i'm sorry,
but if he was welding

93
00:24:19,200 --> 00:24:20,800
And he's allergic
to the chemicals in the flux,

94
00:24:20,800 --> 00:24:22,800
- He could be heading into--
- Anaphylactic shock?

95
00:24:23,200 --> 00:24:25,400
Thanks for the tip,
we got it covered.

96
00:24:27,700 --> 00:24:28,700
Right.

97
00:24:29,900 --> 00:24:31,200
Sorry to butt in.

98
00:24:37,400 --> 00:24:38,400
sam?

99
00:24:39,900 --> 00:24:41,300
- Sam?
- Yeah?

100
00:24:42,100 --> 00:24:43,600
How about that?
2 times in one day.

101
00:24:43,600 --> 00:24:45,300
Got a way of showing up,
don't you?

102
00:24:45,800 --> 00:24:46,700
Sorry.

103
00:24:46,700 --> 00:24:48,400
Now i remember
where i know you from--

104
00:24:48,400 --> 00:24:50,600
The other accident, the one the kid
fell off the roof.

105
00:24:51,200 --> 00:24:52,500
Right, with the broken arm.

106
00:24:52,500 --> 00:24:54,700
Right, which you happened to
know a lot about setting,

107
00:24:54,700 --> 00:24:57,600
I mean, for a civilian.
And now this guy needing adrenalin.

108
00:24:57,700 --> 00:24:59,500
I do a lot of welding, so--

109
00:24:59,600 --> 00:25:01,100
Is that what it is?

110
00:25:01,300 --> 00:25:04,300
You're not some kind of
crash junkie, are you?

111
00:25:06,500 --> 00:25:07,600
No.

112
00:25:08,600 --> 00:25:10,700
Look, it's hard to explain, but...

113
00:25:11,300 --> 00:25:13,700
I promise it won't happen again.
Sorry.

114
00:25:15,100 --> 00:25:16,100
Hey.

115
00:25:18,300 --> 00:25:19,500
It's just that,

116
00:25:19,800 --> 00:25:21,800
You gotta know,
melinda's husband...

117
00:25:22,600 --> 00:25:24,200
He was a friend of mine.

118
00:25:29,700 --> 00:25:32,200
Is he ok? You gonna be fine.
Just keep breathing.

119
00:25:38,900 --> 00:25:41,100
I get where morgan's coming from.
It's brutal.

120
00:25:41,200 --> 00:25:43,900
I mean, the side effects of the drugs
Can be worse than the illness.

121
00:25:44,000 --> 00:25:45,500
So that's what you're researching?

122
00:25:45,600 --> 00:25:47,200
No, i'm trying to find her family.

123
00:25:48,000 --> 00:25:49,000
Why?

124
00:25:49,100 --> 00:25:50,200
I think they should
know about her illness.

125
00:25:50,200 --> 00:25:52,000
You know, maybe they can
convince her to get treatment.

126
00:25:52,000 --> 00:25:53,600
Our ghost can move on,
and who knows,

127
00:25:53,700 --> 00:25:55,000
Maybe morgan will get better.

128
00:25:55,100 --> 00:25:56,700
Yeah, well,
what about her privacy?

129
00:25:56,700 --> 00:25:58,700
Or doctor-Patient confidentiality?

130
00:25:59,800 --> 00:26:01,100
She's not my patient.

131
00:26:01,600 --> 00:26:03,800
But even if she were,
i'd have to weigh my responsibility

132
00:26:03,800 --> 00:26:05,200
To contact the next of kin.

133
00:26:05,800 --> 00:26:08,100
- I think she's dangerously depressed.
- And a liar.

134
00:26:08,600 --> 00:26:11,800
- What?
- Look, morgan's parents died in 2002.

135
00:26:12,900 --> 00:26:15,400
"June and bill jefferies
leave behind their only daughter morgan,

136
00:26:15,400 --> 00:26:17,800
16, a student at melbrook high."

137
00:26:17,900 --> 00:26:19,500
- 16. That's young.
- Yeah.

138
00:26:19,500 --> 00:26:21,000
And she was worried about her family--

139
00:26:21,000 --> 00:26:23,900
Her parents, sisters--
Not wanting to drain them dry.

140
00:26:24,300 --> 00:26:26,800
Well, maybe she found another family

141
00:26:26,800 --> 00:26:29,200
Who adopted her
and they maybe had sisters, too.

142
00:26:29,200 --> 00:26:30,700
Whoa, back up.

143
00:26:33,200 --> 00:26:36,500
I'll tell you what she found--
Husband number one. Schooch.

144
00:26:38,600 --> 00:26:41,100
Ok, a second wedding for both?

145
00:26:41,100 --> 00:26:42,800
Hello, husband number two.

146
00:26:43,800 --> 00:26:46,400
She's a kid!
She's 23.

147
00:26:46,400 --> 00:26:47,500
You're trying to find her husband?

148
00:26:47,500 --> 00:26:49,600
My guess is,
he'd need to find us.

149
00:26:52,600 --> 00:26:53,800
'Cause he's dead.

150
00:26:56,400 --> 00:26:57,700
They both are.

151
00:26:57,800 --> 00:27:00,600
Both of long-Term illnesses.
What are the odds of that?

152
00:27:00,800 --> 00:27:02,000
Pretty good,

153
00:27:02,500 --> 00:27:03,800
If she sought them out.

154
00:27:04,000 --> 00:27:06,400
The cancer support groups,
that's where she found them.

155
00:27:07,200 --> 00:27:08,700
She's a black widow.

156
00:27:27,300 --> 00:27:29,000
- Did you get back into his apartment?
- yeah.

157
00:27:29,000 --> 00:27:30,300
The landlord remembered me.

158
00:27:30,400 --> 00:27:32,700
Rick left morgan
a quarter of a million dollars.

159
00:27:33,000 --> 00:27:35,400
She was his death beneficiary?
How did we miss that?

160
00:27:35,400 --> 00:27:37,300
We didn't look for it,
And i dug through the files.

161
00:27:37,300 --> 00:27:38,700
So what did you find out
at the clinic?

162
00:27:41,000 --> 00:27:44,300
She attended therapy meetings,
But was never a patient.

163
00:27:44,400 --> 00:27:46,300
So she isn't sick now
and never was.

164
00:27:46,400 --> 00:27:48,900
Look, it's not like
i'm fooled by pretty girls every time.

165
00:27:48,900 --> 00:27:50,900
- She seemed so scared.
- Yeah, she was.

166
00:27:50,900 --> 00:27:53,100
She knew that he was haunting her,
And we proved it.

167
00:27:53,300 --> 00:27:55,600
That's why she kept asking
all those questions about the ghost.

168
00:27:55,700 --> 00:27:57,200
Because she didn't know
if he knew.

169
00:27:57,300 --> 00:27:59,000
- And now--
- We don't have much time.

170
00:28:08,300 --> 00:28:10,700
It's too late.
She got away.

171
00:28:10,900 --> 00:28:12,700
She's gonna get away
with everything.

172
00:28:16,700 --> 00:28:18,800
She took my lemon zester.

173
00:28:18,800 --> 00:28:20,800
What did she get away with of yours?

174
00:28:21,900 --> 00:28:24,100
- Did you see morgan before she left?
- Nope.

175
00:28:24,300 --> 00:28:27,800
The building manager said
she had some kind of family emergency;

176
00:28:28,100 --> 00:28:30,800
One that required a nice garnish,
apparently.

177
00:28:30,800 --> 00:28:33,500
You know, we'll just get
a forwarding address from the manager.

178
00:28:33,500 --> 00:28:37,200
I tried. He said she gave him
6 months cash in advance,

179
00:28:37,200 --> 00:28:40,200
So he didn't
ask her for references.

180
00:28:40,700 --> 00:28:42,200
Pretty girls.

181
00:28:42,900 --> 00:28:44,600
They get away with everything.

182
00:28:44,800 --> 00:28:47,600
- You can say that again.
- I say it all the time.

183
00:28:47,600 --> 00:28:49,100
You never listen.

184
00:28:49,800 --> 00:28:52,400
- We haven't met.
- No, we haven't.

185
00:28:52,500 --> 00:28:55,000
- Hi. Melinda.
- How nice.

186
00:28:55,200 --> 00:28:57,200
Another lady friend.

187
00:29:00,300 --> 00:29:02,500
how could i have been so dumb?

188
00:29:04,100 --> 00:29:05,100
Rick?

189
00:29:08,400 --> 00:29:10,000
I should have seen it coming.

190
00:29:11,100 --> 00:29:13,200
- She lied to you.
- Every day.

191
00:29:14,400 --> 00:29:16,700
In group, and afterward
when we were together.

192
00:29:17,300 --> 00:29:18,700
She was so young.

193
00:29:19,300 --> 00:29:21,200
I couldn't believe she was dying.

194
00:29:23,300 --> 00:29:25,100
i couldn't believe
that she cared for me.

195
00:29:25,800 --> 00:29:27,300
But she was so convincing.

196
00:29:28,300 --> 00:29:30,000
Did she ask you for the money?

197
00:29:30,100 --> 00:29:31,700
She didn't have to.

198
00:29:32,500 --> 00:29:35,700
Helping her was the most
important thing on my list, So...

199
00:29:36,900 --> 00:29:38,300
I offered it.

200
00:29:38,700 --> 00:29:40,900
And after that,
something changed.

201
00:29:41,200 --> 00:29:43,200
She started pulling away.

202
00:29:43,400 --> 00:29:44,500
Said she felt ill.

203
00:29:44,500 --> 00:29:46,800
You know, the medication was
making her so sick.

204
00:29:47,100 --> 00:29:49,400
That's why she needed
this other treatment.

205
00:29:49,700 --> 00:29:52,800
This very expensive
other treatment.

206
00:29:55,400 --> 00:29:57,300
She got everything
she wanted.

207
00:29:59,600 --> 00:30:02,000
The only thing
she was sick of is me.

208
00:30:02,900 --> 00:30:05,000
Look, i know that this is painful.

209
00:30:06,100 --> 00:30:07,900
But if you could just forgive...

210
00:30:09,200 --> 00:30:10,700
If you could just let go...

211
00:30:11,400 --> 00:30:13,800
- The light, it'll bring you peace.
- No!

212
00:30:14,700 --> 00:30:16,100
You don't understand.

213
00:30:16,700 --> 00:30:18,700
I died for nothing.

214
00:30:19,400 --> 00:30:21,800
My life meant nothing to her.

215
00:30:23,500 --> 00:30:26,300
And now her life is nothing to me.

216
00:30:30,100 --> 00:30:33,100
not that i blame him, But if
he looked half as angry as he sounded...

217
00:30:33,100 --> 00:30:35,300
Yeah, we have to
get to morgan before he does.

218
00:30:37,000 --> 00:30:38,400
you know where morgan
could have gone,

219
00:30:38,400 --> 00:30:40,100
Maybe with friends or family?

220
00:30:40,200 --> 00:30:41,600
I'm sorry, no.

221
00:30:41,800 --> 00:30:43,200
She was a very private person,

222
00:30:43,200 --> 00:30:46,400
Which is partly why
it just doesn't make any sense.

223
00:30:46,600 --> 00:30:48,800
Half the time, he was the only one
who could get her to share.

224
00:30:49,300 --> 00:30:52,000
Yeah, well, she was just working him.
That was part of the con.

225
00:30:52,200 --> 00:30:53,700
I'm usually a pretty
good judge of character.

226
00:30:53,700 --> 00:30:56,400
She married two others
shortly before they died.

227
00:30:56,400 --> 00:30:58,600
And we're not sure
how many she lied to.

228
00:30:58,800 --> 00:31:01,800
See, that's what doesn't make sense.

229
00:31:02,600 --> 00:31:05,400
I mean, she was just
all about conning these guys,

230
00:31:05,900 --> 00:31:08,800
Then why would she leave us
all that money with rick's name on it?

231
00:31:09,400 --> 00:31:10,700
What are you talking about?

232
00:31:11,100 --> 00:31:14,100
Well, the donation.
It came into the clinic just last week.

233
00:31:14,200 --> 00:31:16,100
How much did she donate,
exactly?

234
00:31:16,200 --> 00:31:17,600
Quarter of a million dollars.

235
00:31:18,400 --> 00:31:20,700
And it could not have
come at a better time, either.

236
00:31:21,600 --> 00:31:23,600
She gave away every penny.

237
00:31:24,500 --> 00:31:26,300
I don't get it,
was she a con artist

238
00:31:26,300 --> 00:31:28,500
Or some kind of
ambulance chasing robin hood?

239
00:31:28,500 --> 00:31:30,700
Yeah, or someone who had
a change of heart,???.

240
00:31:30,800 --> 00:31:33,900
Remember, rick kept saying
that she would withdraw every time he left,

241
00:31:33,900 --> 00:31:36,000
So maybe her conscience
was getting to her.

242
00:31:36,000 --> 00:31:37,900
Hey, you know what else
wants to get to her right now?

243
00:31:38,000 --> 00:31:39,000
Our ghost.

244
00:31:39,100 --> 00:31:40,800
And he's M.A.D.,
mad.

245
00:31:40,800 --> 00:31:43,000
So if you were her,
where would you go?

246
00:31:43,100 --> 00:31:45,600
I don't know.
Next small town with a cancer ward.

247
00:31:45,900 --> 00:31:48,000
No, her conscience is getting to her.

248
00:31:48,000 --> 00:31:49,500
She'd be stupid to stick around.

249
00:31:49,700 --> 00:31:50,900
Or maybe not.

250
00:31:51,100 --> 00:31:53,500
You know,I mean, she can run from us,
but she can't from rick.

251
00:31:53,500 --> 00:31:55,700
She knows that his spirit
is still here. Maybe...

252
00:31:56,600 --> 00:31:58,500
maybe she's trying to make it up to him.

253
00:31:58,700 --> 00:32:00,600
- The list.
- Yeah, it's a long shot,

254
00:32:00,600 --> 00:32:03,100
But what hadn't he
marked off?

255
00:32:03,600 --> 00:32:05,600
Well, the denver omelet
did catch my eye,

256
00:32:05,600 --> 00:32:08,700
Only because i tried, and it's very hard
To get the ham and the bell pepper ratio.

257
00:32:08,700 --> 00:32:11,100
A place she could go--
In grandview.

258
00:32:16,200 --> 00:32:17,500
The lunar eclipse.

259
00:32:18,000 --> 00:32:20,700
It's happening right now.
That was on the list, right?

260
00:32:22,200 --> 00:32:24,900
Look, everyone is trying to
find a place to watch.

261
00:32:25,100 --> 00:32:26,100
- Come on!
- The roof!

262
00:32:26,100 --> 00:32:27,600
They used to go up there, together.

263
00:33:07,900 --> 00:33:10,600
There was a time i would have thought
you were crying for me.

264
00:33:12,200 --> 00:33:14,100
I believed every lie you told me.

265
00:33:14,700 --> 00:33:16,500
How could i be so stupid?

266
00:33:28,300 --> 00:33:30,700
Help!
Please! Help!

267
00:33:32,100 --> 00:33:33,400
Help me, please ???!

268
00:33:35,400 --> 00:33:36,900
???

269
00:33:51,000 --> 00:33:52,100
Where is she?

270
00:33:52,500 --> 00:33:54,500
She's finding out
what it felt like.

271
00:34:04,200 --> 00:34:05,800
???

272
00:34:06,400 --> 00:34:07,400
Help me!

273
00:34:07,600 --> 00:34:09,600
Help me, please!
Someone!

274
00:34:13,900 --> 00:34:15,100
Please, please!

275
00:34:19,200 --> 00:34:21,700
hello, hello?

276
00:34:22,500 --> 00:34:24,500
Is somebody there? Help!

277
00:34:25,000 --> 00:34:27,800
- Morgan?!
- Oh! Please help me!
- We got you, morgan.

278
00:34:27,800 --> 00:34:29,200
We got you, ok,
we got you!

279
00:34:29,300 --> 00:34:30,600
- Hang on!
- Please don't drop me!

280
00:34:30,600 --> 00:34:31,600
We won't drop you,

281
00:34:33,300 --> 00:34:35,900
- you're ok...
- We got you. We won't drop you.
- Please don't drop me!

282
00:34:38,500 --> 00:34:39,900
it's ok.

283
00:34:40,000 --> 00:34:42,000
You're going to be ok.
It's ok.

284
00:34:42,500 --> 00:34:43,900
That was rick, wasn't it?

285
00:34:44,000 --> 00:34:45,200
He's trying to kill me!

286
00:34:45,300 --> 00:34:47,000
It's ok, we're here now.
He can't hurt you.

287
00:34:47,200 --> 00:34:50,100
I didn't try to kill her.
I tried to teach her.

288
00:34:50,500 --> 00:34:51,900
He's angry.

289
00:34:51,900 --> 00:34:54,400
All right? He wants to punish you.
Do you understand why?

290
00:34:56,100 --> 00:34:57,100
Yeah.

291
00:34:57,500 --> 00:34:59,800
But what can i do?
I mean, it's done.

292
00:35:00,200 --> 00:35:01,700
I lied to him.

293
00:35:01,800 --> 00:35:02,900
But why?

294
00:35:03,400 --> 00:35:04,900
Was the money
that important to her?

295
00:35:04,900 --> 00:35:06,100
Look, he's here.

296
00:35:06,700 --> 00:35:09,100
Morgan, this is your chance
to explain things.

297
00:35:17,900 --> 00:35:20,300
I don't know why
i do the things i do.

298
00:35:20,400 --> 00:35:21,500
Ok.

299
00:35:21,700 --> 00:35:24,000
But do you understand
Why this time is different?

300
00:35:25,000 --> 00:35:26,600
But he was different.

301
00:35:27,500 --> 00:35:31,200
I mean, he cared about me.
He really cared about me.

302
00:35:31,400 --> 00:35:32,500
You know?

303
00:35:33,400 --> 00:35:35,700
And he didn't want
anything from me, and...

304
00:35:37,800 --> 00:35:39,500
I had never had that before.

305
00:35:46,700 --> 00:35:48,100
Is that true?

306
00:35:49,200 --> 00:35:50,700
I think you had that before.

307
00:35:51,900 --> 00:35:53,400
But they left you,

308
00:35:53,900 --> 00:35:55,500
When you were really young.

309
00:35:57,500 --> 00:35:59,900
This all started
after your parents died, right?

310
00:36:05,800 --> 00:36:07,500
There were foster homes

311
00:36:07,500 --> 00:36:10,600
and schools i couldn't finish, And...

312
00:36:12,200 --> 00:36:14,200
I just learned to fight for things.

313
00:36:15,300 --> 00:36:17,900
And then, i guess,
just to take them.

314
00:36:20,300 --> 00:36:22,100
Things i had no right to.

315
00:36:24,100 --> 00:36:25,800
People's feelings.

316
00:36:26,800 --> 00:36:29,200
And i know that it doesn't
make it right.

317
00:36:30,000 --> 00:36:32,000
It's no excuse,
but giving the money back,

318
00:36:32,000 --> 00:36:34,700
It was the only thing
i knew to do.

319
00:36:36,100 --> 00:36:37,700
I--I don't understand.

320
00:36:38,800 --> 00:36:41,100
- You gave that money away?
- all of it.

321
00:36:41,300 --> 00:36:43,100
To a cancer clinic in your name.

322
00:36:45,400 --> 00:36:46,500
well.

323
00:36:48,000 --> 00:36:49,500
It's better than keeping it.

324
00:36:51,800 --> 00:36:53,500
- I still died for a lie.
- What?

325
00:36:53,500 --> 00:36:56,200
- What is he saying?
- I'm not sure.

326
00:36:56,200 --> 00:36:59,200
Yes, she lied.
Ok, but she didn't make you sick.

327
00:36:59,200 --> 00:37:01,000
- You died because--
- Look, it doesn't matter.

328
00:37:01,000 --> 00:37:02,500
No, it does matter.

329
00:37:06,400 --> 00:37:08,600
It's the reason that
you packed your chute wrong that day.

330
00:37:08,600 --> 00:37:10,600
That's how you knew
you were going to die so soon.

331
00:37:11,700 --> 00:37:13,700
It wasn't an accident, was it.

332
00:37:15,600 --> 00:37:16,600
What?

