00:39:25,700 --> 00:39:26,700
Ok.

364
00:40:20,900 --> 00:40:21,900
He's gone.

365
00:40:22,600 --> 00:40:24,100
He went into the light.

366
00:40:25,100 --> 00:40:26,200
That light?

367
00:40:48,300 --> 00:40:50,900
There you are.
All the lights were off.

368
00:40:50,900 --> 00:40:52,200
I didn't know
if you were home.

369
00:40:52,700 --> 00:40:55,200
Yeah, you know,
i was, uh, thinking.

370
00:40:55,300 --> 00:40:56,600
Oh, really? About what?

371
00:40:56,600 --> 00:40:59,500
- Oh, it's been a weird day.
- Ok, so tell me everything.

372
00:41:01,000 --> 00:41:03,800
Well, it was like having my whole life
Pass before my eyes.

373
00:41:04,200 --> 00:41:06,900
I mean, old friends on the street, my job,

374
00:41:07,700 --> 00:41:08,900
Everything.

375
00:41:09,800 --> 00:41:12,100
Then i realized
it's not mine anymore.

376
00:41:12,500 --> 00:41:15,400
- I mean, that life is over.
- Hey.

377
00:41:15,700 --> 00:41:16,900
Don't say that.

378
00:41:17,000 --> 00:41:18,800
Ok? We'll get it back.
It might take us some time--

379
00:41:18,800 --> 00:41:20,500
No, it's all right.
You know, because...

380
00:41:21,200 --> 00:41:22,600
What if i want something different?

381
00:41:23,300 --> 00:41:25,900
Different? How?

382
00:41:27,500 --> 00:41:29,800
Did i ever tell you why
i became a paramedic?

383
00:41:29,800 --> 00:41:31,600
Yeah, 'cause you wanted
to help people.

384
00:41:31,600 --> 00:41:34,100
Right. But what i really wanted
Was to become a doctor,

385
00:41:34,600 --> 00:41:36,600
And i just didn't have the patience.

386
00:41:36,900 --> 00:41:38,600
So i took a shortcut.

387
00:41:38,600 --> 00:41:40,500
And as much
as i love the work,

388
00:41:41,100 --> 00:41:42,700
I wish that i'd taken the time.

389
00:41:43,500 --> 00:41:46,100
Well, now all you have is time.

390
00:41:47,100 --> 00:41:48,600
I got more than that.

391
00:41:50,800 --> 00:41:53,100
First of all, remember all
the annoying prerequisites

392
00:41:53,100 --> 00:41:55,300
For med school i was trying to
find space for last year?

393
00:41:55,400 --> 00:41:56,400
- Yes.
- Yeah?

394
00:41:57,400 --> 00:41:59,800
Well, it turns out
that i've already studied them.

395
00:42:00,300 --> 00:42:01,600
What are you talking about?

396
00:42:01,800 --> 00:42:03,500
When sam was getting his
architecture degree,

397
00:42:03,500 --> 00:42:05,900
He took all these math
and science classes.

398
00:42:06,800 --> 00:42:08,700
These are his college transcripts.

399
00:42:08,700 --> 00:42:10,900
Yeah, which i had faxed
over earlier today,

400
00:42:10,900 --> 00:42:13,600
And, i mean, of course i have to study them
so i understand them myself,

401
00:42:13,600 --> 00:42:16,500
But this could save a year.

402
00:42:17,100 --> 00:42:18,300
Med school?

403
00:42:18,400 --> 00:42:19,800
You're gonna go to med school?

404
00:42:19,800 --> 00:42:22,100
Well, if i can get in and if
we can figure out a way to pay for it.

405
00:42:22,100 --> 00:42:24,900
Hey, we'll manage.

406
00:42:25,900 --> 00:42:28,000
Yeah.
Yeah.

407
00:42:29,900 --> 00:42:32,500
Do you know the 2 things
i've dreamt of most of in my life?

408
00:42:34,200 --> 00:42:35,500
Being a doctor,

409
00:42:36,400 --> 00:42:37,400
And you.

410
00:42:38,500 --> 00:42:40,600
What if i just work hard enough,

411
00:42:40,700 --> 00:42:42,900
- And if i'm patient...
- Hey.

412
00:42:44,100 --> 00:42:47,400
You don't have to work hard for me,
And you don't have to be patient.

413
00:42:53,400 --> 00:42:55,600
Ah, nobody should be as lucky as me.

414
00:42:56,400 --> 00:42:57,900
Twice in one lifetime.

415
00:42:58,700 --> 00:43:00,000
Actually...

